From d492d14f8f205ee40c31d85087e918eaea9c71d0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramasamy Kaliappan <rkaliapp@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Oct 2025 21:47:09 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Skip pruning of unauthorized STA in
 partner link

In scenarios where an MLD AP receives authentication/association requests
on link0 from a non mld station, the connection may fail,
resulting in a STA entry that remains unauthorized.

Later, when the same station connects successfully to link1 of
the same MLD AP after completing 4-way handshake, the current design
checks for the STA in the partner link and prunes the association in
the partner hapd.

However, the current logic does not skip pruning when the STA is
unauthorized in the partner link, leading stale STA entry in partner hapd.

Adds a fix to skip pruning and STA removal in the partner hapd when
the STA is unauthorized.

Patch-dependency: NA
Patch-work: NA

Signed-off-by: Ramasamy Kaliappan <rkaliapp@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11.c | 14 ++------------
 src/ap/sta_info.c   |  4 +---
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)

--- a/src/ap/sta_info.c
+++ b/src/ap/sta_info.c
@@ -778,8 +778,7 @@ int skip_prune_for_partner_links(struct
 			continue;
 
 		link_sta = ap_get_sta(lhapd, sta->addr);
-		if (link_sta &&
-		    ap_sta_is_authorized(sta)) {
+		if (link_sta) {
 			if (!sta->mld_info.mld_sta ||
 			    !link_sta->mld_info.mld_sta) {
 				wpa_printf(MSG_DEBUG,
